name: Google Building C
address: Google Building C, 747 6th St South Building C, Kirkland, WA 98033, United States

detailed_reviews.review_text: Normally, I wouldnt write a review about a corporate building, however, whats interesting about this place is that there are several public parks as well as a running trail that go right through the center of the campus. Its kind of neat to be able to see how the Google employees live at work, well, enjoying some very well maintained public park facilities. There is also a train which is an homage to the old train line that used to run through here. This place is actually interesting to visit if youre in the area and taking a long run or jog.
What a place to work!  So close to the water body,  great running trail, a public volleyball court, kids zip-lining, a soccer field and a big open garden at the centre.
Great! They have a lovely field and trail that you can walk or ride your bike on, and stretches very far! Building it cool, and they have beach volleyball, and some cool gym stuff as well.

Did you know they have an old locomotive there? Great landscaping. Awesome playground nearby. Access to the boardwalk. Weve been there around Christmas - and enjoyed the Christmas tree and the lights.
Great place. I love the fact they had a place to keep their dog and kids to play.
Amazing people, phenomenal food! The best leadership on the planet!

This looks like a fun and invigorating place to work. Lots of quiet space to go to work if you find the open office concept too distracting. The employee lunch rooms are some of the best I have seen inside an office complex.
Nice office design, very spacious!

Recently invited by friend who works there.  In a word... WOW, sign me up!  I can see why everyone wants to work at Google.  Awesome campus: incredible views, nice architecture, cool vibe, snacks and drinks galore, other perks too.  If I worked there Id probably be working more hours than I have anywhere else. We had lunch, which was excellent.  Got some fresh brewed lattes and he gave me a nice walking tour.  I wish I had taken some pictures but didnt want to be a total tourist.

I have not been inside the Google Kirkland Campus but I have worked in the neighborhood. Every interaction that Ive had with employees have been positive and I hear nothing but good things about Google the workplace. I do like the programs that Google offers such as Local Guides and Street View. They give me the opportunity to contribute to Google Maps and hopefully make a difference for someone. In a small way I feel like I am part of the Google team and I like that. - Thanks

Disclaimer: I work here. Integrates well with the surrounding area. The Cross Kirkland Corridor splits the campus and is open to the public. There are large grassy areas to relax on, a playground for children, and various sports courts and fields. Lots of fun things to do and discover if youre allowed inside.

I attended a free, all-day workshop and it was great! They treat you like you work there and the presenters all have the knowledge and passion of true Googlers. Not to mention, their campus is beautiful - Not quite like their Mountain View location, but still great!

Ive been here multiple times for meetings and a couple times to meet friends for lunch. Each time Ive had a great experience. The absolute best thing though was the Google Lights event that I attended in December 2016!

Great little park in Googles campus, along the cross Kirkland corridor. They have a small playground with zip line, beach volleyball court, basketball courts, and some tables and chairs. Super clean and can get quite busy.

Visited as a guest of one of the Architects working on the buildings.  Great learning experience for me as an architecture student!  I didnt get a chance to try out the UXP room in the lobby, but I understand thats open to everybody, no invitation needed.

This is great place to visit and work at. Although I dont personally work there, I know a few people who do. What impresses me the most is the companies ethic and mora value meter. I would say from an outsiders viewpoint is Be good to each other is something that is done and not just said.

Google campus is a really fun place to visit. Inspiring to see all the cool projects employees get to work on. Beautiful office, with the Cross Kirkland Corridor trail running through the center of campus.
The campus looks great.  Theres playground for little kids as well as a volleyball and soccer field for the grownups.  Ample amount of parking for visitors.
The atmosphere at this office is great.  Employees look content, and productive.  The size of the office allows for an assortment of teams while still retaining the startup business type feel.
Nice layout of the campus with the Cross Kirkland corridor running between building D and the other three buildings. Food is great at the cafes, particularly the sandwiches in Building B.
They have 3 cafeterias, nap room, free drinks at any time all day, comfortable individual and group seating, coffee shops, and much more. They spoil their employees.
Very nice office. Very family and pet oriented. I especially like the coffee lab microkitchen. You do need an employee to check you in, though.

Wish List!  WOW!  Googles Kirkland,WA few blocks from NorthWest University as well as Beautiful Kirkland Waterfront.  The visitors parking has constantly been FULL.  Amazing white buildings. Saw on Y E L P reviews of inside; not in person but via online photos; amazing smart place where one could even take ones puppy to work!  I am ENVI OU S!
There are 4 buildings overall. Theres public park/space between the older cluster of buildings and the new one. The Cross Kirkland Corridor cuts through it. Awesome company, awesome office buildings.
